doc.after: Marojejy National Park is best known for its two iconic species, the helmet vanga (Euryceros prevostii)[13][32] and the critically endangered silky sifaka or simpona (Propithecus candidus).[18][25][33] The silky sifaka has been listed as one of "The World's 25 Most Endangered Primates" since the inception of the list in 2000.[34] According to estimates, fewer than 1,000 individuals of this species remain, and none exist in captivity.[26]
